text: Small question: are we sure that there is no difference between fcp-indi and fcp-indi-new?

> I think we should go with "fcp-indi-new" since the main project has the same name.

I know that it is the new URL but what is the difference with the previous one? Maybe the used an update version of CPAC for the preproc? I just would like to be sure that we are still fetching the same data.
I think that taking the md5 hash of a bucnh of random files should be enough. Or maybe @Joaoloula can grab Cameron at brainhack and ask him ? :P
So, let's go merging this one when all is green.
Merging as it makes doc better (independently of the subjects / n_subjects debate).

Cameron's not here :/ In the middle of testing, I actually overwrote the dataset coming from the old download link, so I can't compare the checksums, can someone who still has the 'old' data take care of that?

So @AlexandreAbraham got in touch with the Child Mind Institute people and, long story short, the fcp-indi-new does have exactly the same data as fcp-indi, but it was just a temporary switch they made. The old link is now up and running again, and so I reverted this part of the PR.
